flowchart TD
    accTitle: DISCOVER discovery loop
    accDescr: The goal command sets a standing objective, then market-scan proposes candidates, scores them on the market taxonomy, kills weak ones, challenges survivors, and verdicts each KEEP, PARK, or KILL. KILL and PARK loop back via the loop command to propose again; KEEP exits as a validated opportunity handed to the ideate.

    GOAL["/discovery-goal · set standing objective"]
    PROPOSE["/market-scan · propose 3–5 candidates"]
    SCORE["score on market taxonomy · severity · demand · size · WTP · pricing power · competition · reachability · stack-fit"]
    KILLWEAK["KILL the weak candidates"]
    CHALLENGE["challenge the survivors"]
    VERDICT{"verdict?"}
    KEEP(["KEEP — the spark"])
    OUT[/"VALIDATED OPPORTUNITY · scorecard + evidence + verdict"/]
    IDEATE[["handed to ideate"]]

    GOAL --> PROPOSE
    PROPOSE --> SCORE
    SCORE --> KILLWEAK
    KILLWEAK --> CHALLENGE
    CHALLENGE --> VERDICT
    VERDICT -- "KILL / PARK → re-propose · /loop /market-scan" --> PROPOSE
    VERDICT -- "KEEP" --> KEEP
    KEEP --> OUT
    OUT --> IDEATE

    classDef kill fill:#3a2230,stroke:#f7768e,stroke-width:2px,color:#f7768e;
    classDef park fill:#3a3322,stroke:#e0af68,stroke-width:2px,color:#e0af68;
    classDef keep fill:#26331f,stroke:#9ece6a,stroke-width:2px,color:#9ece6a;
    class KILLWEAK kill;
    class VERDICT park;
    class KEEP,OUT keep;
